			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Role Objective</strong><br />
<br />
The Firm is seeking to recruit bright and passionate individuals (Senior Consultant, Assistant Manager) who have relevant work experience and skills in FSRM domain. The role will primarily involve executing or managing client engagements in FSRM. The role is regional in nature and has vacancies across the region (UAE, Bahrain, Kuwait).<br />
<br />
<br />
<strong>Role Responsibilities</strong><br />
The key responsibilities of the candidate include:<br />
&nbsp;<br />
1. Understanding the client&rsquo;s requirements and writing clear client proposals that articulate the specialized domain skills.<br />
<br />
2. Conducting interviews with clients (senior staff ‐ CXOs &amp; heads of business units), analyzing the facts, establishing hypotheses, &amp; deriving conclusions.<br />
<br />
3. Delivering concise deliverables that are tailored to the client&rsquo;s business, and requirements, in a timely fashion.<br />
<br />
In addition, managerial candidates with have the following responsibilities:<br />
<br />
1. Managing the engagement (staff, time, client) to achieve high‐quality deliverables, on time<br />
2. Creating new business opportunities by presenting specific value propositions to clients, or preparing collateral packs<br />
3. Coaching and mentoring team members providing technical direction and guidance.<br />
<br />
<br />
<strong>Required Skills&nbsp;</strong><br />
The candidate will have experience in one of the following areas:<br />
&nbsp;<br />
1. Implementing Basel 2 (Pillar 1, Pillar 2 requirements)/ Basel 3/ Solvency 2&nbsp;<br />
2. Implementing the corporate governance standards in banks and investment banks &ndash; board focused initiatives aligning to regulatory best‐practices<br />
3. Establishing a risk governance structure with clear roles and responsibilities<br />
4. Setting quantitative risk tolerances and limit structures &ndash; cascading of appetites<br />
5. Developing risk policies and processes in credit, market, operational risks, ALM tailored to the specific business line<br />
6. Deep understanding of credit life cycle (underwriting &amp; approvals), and experience in credit rating &amp; analysis + approvals<br />
7. Solid understanding of investment life‐cycle in asset allocation and its link to appetite setting, pre and post‐investment due‐diligence&nbsp;<br />
8. Implementing operational risk frameworks with solid understanding of process maps, risks and controls &ndash; deep product knowledge is essential&nbsp;<br />
9. Conducting Fraud Scenario Assessments in FS clients &ndash; banks and investment banks&nbsp;<br />
10. Quantitative modeling: rating models, Value at Risk, pricing, economic capital, stress testing, RAPM&nbsp;<br />
11. Implementing risk IT systems (at‐least 1 implementation or experience in Product Management)<br />
<br />
12. Implementing Enterprise Risk Management frameworks across multiple FS clients (stock exchanges, investment companies).<br />
2<br />
<br />
<br />
<strong>Work Experience &amp; Education</strong><br />
Candidates will 2 to 5 years professional experience in any of the following:<br />
<br />
1. Risk Management function or Line Business of a commercial bank, investment bank or an insurance firm (credit, market, operational and ALM)<br />
<br />
2. Leading consulting firms, specializing in FS or working in rating agencies<br />
3. Experience in implementing leading risk vendor solutions (Sungard, Algorithmics, Misys, Moodys).<br />
<br />
<br />
Manager level candidates will have over 6‐7 years of relevant experience.<br />
<br />
Ideal educational qualifications would be:<br />
<br />
1. Phd. (Math, Physics, Economics, Finance)<br />
<br />
2. MBA (Finance) + under‐graduation in a quantitative discipline (preferably engineering, mathematics, statistics) or Post Graduation in any of the above‐mentioned areas<br />
3. Professional qualification (Chartered Accountancy) with relevant risk management work experience, or certifications like FRM, PRM, CFA, CAIA, ACT.<br />
<br />
<br />
Expected Travel&nbsp;<br />
The role is regional in nature, highly travel‐intensive, and would require candidates to spend 40‐50% of the time in client engagements (within the GCC region).</p>
