POSITION:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Senior Manager &ndash; Internal Audit<br />
REPORTS TO:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Internal Audit Associate Director or Above<br />
The following statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed. This is not intended to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required of personnel.</p>
<p>
JOB DESCRIPTION</p>
<p>
OVERALL RESPONSIBILITY</p>
<p>
Responsible for execution on client engagements and maintaining a strong relationship with senior client personnel.&nbsp; Must have a solid understanding of their client&rsquo;s business and be able to demonstrate technical competence in their product group and industry.&nbsp; Ensure quality and satisfaction on engagements.&nbsp; Must be able to clearly articulate the value drivers of our business, and are responsible for developing opportunities both at existing clients and new clients. Responsible for job economics and for ensuring timely close and billing of projects.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
EDUCATIONAL &amp; PROFESSIONAL CREDENTIALS</p>
<p>
&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in relevant discipline (e.g. Accounting, Finance or Business Related field) required<br />
&bull; 9+ years in a related field, preferably in professional services and/or industry<br />
&bull; Professional Certification such as CPA, CIA, CISA strongly preferred<br />
&bull; &ldquo;Big 4&rdquo; experience in Internal Audit, strongly preferred<br />
&bull; Telecom industry experience preferred</p>
<p>
REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE &amp; SKILLS</p>
<p>
&bull; Prior management&nbsp; and direct supervisory experience in a team environment<br />
&bull; Must work well in a team-oriented environment as well as independently<br />
&bull; Must work creatively and analytically in a problem-solving environment<br />
&bull; Demonstrated excellent leadership and interpersonal skills<br />
&bull; Demonstrated advanced written and verbal communication skills<br />
&bull; Must have ability to multi-task<br />
&bull; Excellent project management skills<br />
&bull; Excellent client relationship skills<br />
&bull; Proven Business Development skills<br />
&bull; Excellent time management skills<br />
&bull; Demonstrated mentoring and people development skills<br />
&bull; Must be able to handle highly confidential information in a strictly professional manner<br />
&bull; Must be able to maintain professional demeanor in times of high stress</p>
<p>
REQUIRED TECHNICAL KNOWLEDGE &amp; SKILLS</p>
<p>
&bull; Specialized Industry skills<br />
&bull; Solid knowledge of auditing processes and methodologies, including flowcharting<br />
&bull; Solid understanding of current accounting and auditing principles<br />
&bull; Solid understanding of internal control concepts (COSO, COBIT)<br />
&bull; Proficient in Microsoft Office suite applications</p>
<p>
ABILITY TO TRAVEL</p>
<p>
&bull; Travel throughout the month frequently required based on client requests/commitments</p>
